(122, 132, 'Publication', NULL, '0', '1', 'https://revistas.unl.edu.ec/index.php/cedamaz/article/view/237', ';;EUHEC9gAAAAJ;', 43, '/scholar?q=info:tBdkk1uAH8kJ:scholar.google.com/&output=cite&scirp=0&hl=en', '/citations?hl=en&xsrf=&continue=/scholar%3Fq%3D%2BAyala,%2BL.,%2BVilla,%2BM.,%2BAguirre,%2BZ.,%2BAguirre,%2BN.,%2BCuantificaci%25C3%2583%25C2%25B3n%2Bdel%2Bcarbono%2Ben%2Blos%2Bp%25C3%2583%25C2%25A1ramos%2Bdel%2Bparque%2Bnacional%2BYacuri,%2Bprovincias%2Bde%2BLoja%2By%2BZamora%2BChinchipe,%2BEcuador%2B(2014)%2BCedamaz,%2B4%2B(1),%2Bpp.%2B45-52%26hl%3Den%26as_sdt%3D0,33&citilm=1&json=&update_op=library_add&info=tBdkk1uAH8kJ&ei=J3OTYOa2AsKLy9YPvcOdyAo', '/scholar?cites=14492443256704735156&as_sdt=5,33&sciodt=0,33&hl=en', '/scholar?q=related:tBdkk1uAH8kJ:scholar.google.com/&scioq=+Ayala,+L.,+Villa,+M.,+Aguirre,+Z.,+Aguirre,+N.,+Cuantificaci%C3%83%C2%B3n+del+carbono+en+los+p%C3%83%C2%A1ramos+del+parque+nacional+Yacuri,+provincias+de+Loja+y+Zamora+Chinchipe,+Ecuador+(2014)+Cedamaz,+4+(1),+pp.+45-52&hl=en&as_sdt=0,33', 'Cuantificación del carbono en los páramos del parque nacional Yacuri, provincias de Loja y Zamora Chinchipe, Ecuador', 'L Ayala;M Villa;ZA Mendoza;NA Mendoza', 2014, 'Cedamaz', 'Se determinó los tipos de cobertura vegetal del Parque Nacional Yacuri y, para los páramos arbustivo y herbáceo se determinó respectivamente su composición y estructura, incluyendo el carbono jado en la biomasa, necromasa y suelo y, la in uencia de la biomasa en los contenidos de carbono jado en el suelo; usando parcelas temporales de 4 m2 y 1 m2. Los tipos de cobertura vegetal presentes son páramo arbustivo, páramo herbáceo, bosque siempreverde montano alto, bosque de neblina montano, bosque chaparro'),
(123, 133, 'Publication', NULL, '0', '1', 'https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF00155524', '', 142, '/scholar?q=info:xt0hX6MLm-0J:scholar.google.com/&output=cite&scirp=0&hl=en', '/citations?hl=en&xsrf=&continue=/scholar%3Fq%3D%2BHofstede,%2BR.,%2BThe%2Beffects%2Bof%2Bgrazing%2Band%2Bburning%2Bon%2Bsoil%2Band%2Bplant%2Bnutrient%2Bconcentrations%2Bin%2BColombian%2BParamo%2Bgrasslands%2B(1995)%2BPlant%2BSoil,%2B173%2B(1),%2Bpp.%2B111-132.%2B,%2BCOI:%2B1:CAS:528:DyaK2MXntlWisb8%25253D%26hl%3Den%26as_sdt%3D0,33&citilm=1&json=&update_op=library_add&info=xt0hX6MLm-0J&ei=KXOTYN-DLZWSmgGbq7y4AQ', '/scholar?cites=17121291204682702278&as_sdt=5,33&sciodt=0,33&hl=en', '/scholar?q=related:xt0hX6MLm-0J:scholar.google.com/&scioq=+Hofstede,+R.,+The+effects+of+grazing+and+burning+on+soil+and+plant+nutrient+concentrations+in+Colombian+Paramo+grasslands+(1995)+Plant+Soil,+173+(1),+pp.+111-132.+,+COI:+1:CAS:528:DyaK2MXntlWisb8%253D&hl=en&as_sdt=0,33', 'The effects of grazing and burning on soil and plant nutrient concentrations in Colombian páramo grasslands', 'RGM Hofstede', 1995, 'Plant and Soil', 'The impact of extensive livestock farming on the physical and chemical characteristics of the volcanic soils and on the nutrient status of green plant tissues of neotropical alpine grasslands (páramo) is studied. Soil and plant samples were taken over a one-year period at five sites with different agricultural (grazing and burning) management. In the undisturbed páramo ecosystem, soil moisture (50–250%) and organic matter content are high (7–27%) and decomposition (11–35% yr-1) and element concentrations are low. Low temperatures'),
(124, 135, 'Publication', NULL, '0', '1', 'https://www.jstor.org/stable/3673257', '', 35, '/scholar?q=info:Tbc20CPUelIJ:scholar.google.com/&output=cite&scirp=0&hl=en', '/citations?hl=en&xsrf=&continue=/scholar%3Fq%3D%2BMorris,%2BA.,%2BForestry%2Band%2Bland-use%2Bconflicts%2Bin%2BCuenca,%2BEcuador%2B(1985)%2BMt%2BRes%2BDev,%2B5%2B(2),%2Bp.%2B183%26hl%3Den%26as_sdt%3D0,33&citilm=1&json=&update_op=library_add&info=Tbc20CPUelIJ&ei=T3OTYKbnAsKLy9YPvcOdyAo', '/scholar?cites=5943295908550981453&as_sdt=5,33&sciodt=0,33&hl=en', '/scholar?q=related:Tbc20CPUelIJ:scholar.google.com/&scioq=+Morris,+A.,+Forestry+and+land-use+conflicts+in+Cuenca,+Ecuador+(1985)+Mt+Res+Dev,+5+(2),+p.+183&hl=en&as_sdt=0,33', 'Forestry and land-use conflicts in Cuenca, Ecuador', 'A Morris', 1985, 'Mountain Research and Development', 'Forestry is very generally regarded as\" good\" in ecological and rural development terms, and as something to be promoted. This paper reviews a case study of one area where forestry may not be entirely positive in its effects and may produce conflicts with other land uses, as well as with ecological and employment aims. The latter part of the study points out some modifications which could be made to the afforestation programme which would make it more compatible with other land uses; this includes the introduction of agro-forestry or'),
(125, 136, 'Publication', NULL, '0', '1', 'https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/15230430.2000.12003334', ';;rYSRUHIAAAAJ', 284, '/scholar?q=info:3D7ChHrBXWAJ:scholar.google.com/&output=cite&scirp=0&hl=en', '/citations?hl=en&xsrf=&continue=/scholar%3Fq%3D%2BPaulsen,%2BJ.,%2BWeber,%2BU.M.,%2BK%25C3%2583%25C2%25B6rner,%2BC.,%2BTree%2Bgrowth%2Bnear%2Btreeline:%2Babrupt%2Bor%2Bgradual%2Breduction%2Bwith%2Baltitude%253F%2B(2000)%2BArctic%2BAntarct%2BAlp%2BRes,%2B32%2B(1),%2Bpp.%2B14-20%26hl%3Den%26as_sdt%3D0,33&citilm=1&json=&update_op=library_add&info=3D7ChHrBXWAJ&ei=UHOTYMrtNY3nmQGp8JOQCQ', '/scholar?cites=6943918932432666332&as_sdt=5,33&sciodt=0,33&hl=en', '/scholar?q=related:3D7ChHrBXWAJ:scholar.google.com/&scioq=+Paulsen,+J.,+Weber,+U.M.,+K%C3%83%C2%B6rner,+C.,+Tree+growth+near+treeline:+abrupt+or+gradual+reduction+with+altitude%3F+(2000)+Arctic+Antarct+Alp+Res,+32+(1),+pp.+14-20&hl=en&as_sdt=0,33', 'Tree growth near treeline: abrupt or gradual reduction with altitude?', 'J Paulsen;UM Weber;C Körner', 2000, 'Arctic, Antarctic, and Alpine …', 'Natural climatic treelines are relatively discrete boundaries in the landscape established at a certain elevation within an otherwise continuous gradient of environmental change. By studying tree rings along elevational transects at and below the upper treeline in the European Alps, we (1) determine whether radial stem growth declines abruptly or gradually, and (2) test climatic influences on trees near treeline by investigating transects for climatically different historical periods. While tree height decreases gradually toward the'),
(126, 137, 'Publication', NULL, '0', '1', 'https://www.jstor.org/stable/40665234', ';;;', 151, '/scholar?q=info:0EkbelLagCEJ:scholar.google.com/&output=cite&scirp=0&hl=en', '/citations?hl=en&xsrf=&continue=/scholar%3Fq%3D%2BNiiyama,%2BK.,%2BKajimoto,%2BT.,%2BMatsuura,%2BY.,%2BYamashita,%2BT.,%2BMatsuo,%2BN.,%2BYashiro,%2BY.,%2BEstimation%2Bof%2Broot%2Bbiomass%2Bbased%2Bon%2Bexcavation%2Bof%2Bindividual%2Broot%2Bsystems%2Bin%2Ba%2Bprimary%2Bdipterocarp%2Bforest%2Bin%2BPasoh%2BForest%2BReserve,%2BPeninsular%2BMalaysia%2B(2010)%2BJ%2BTrop%2BEcol,%2B26%2B%26hl%3Den%26as_sdt%3D0,33&citilm=1&json=&update_op=library_add&info=0EkbelLagCEJ&ei=U3OTYLHeE4XSmAG-8pPwBw', '/scholar?cites=2414169448041368016&as_sdt=5,33&sciodt=0,33&hl=en', '/scholar?q=related:0EkbelLagCEJ:scholar.google.com/&scioq=+Niiyama,+K.,+Kajimoto,+T.,+Matsuura,+Y.,+Yamashita,+T.,+Matsuo,+N.,+Yashiro,+Y.,+Estimation+of+root+biomass+based+on+excavation+of+individual+root+systems+in+a+primary+dipterocarp+forest+in+Pasoh+Forest+Reserve,+Peninsular+Malaysia+(2010)+J+Trop+Ecol,+26+&hl=en&as_sdt=0,33', 'Estimation of root biomass based on excavation of individual root systems in a primary dipterocarp forest in Pasoh Forest Reserve, Peninsular Malaysia', 'K Niiyama;T Kajimoto;Y Matsuura;T Yamashita', 2010, 'Journal of Tropical …', 'Precise estimation of root biomass is important for understanding carbon stocks and dynamics in tropical rain forests. However, limited information is available on individual root masses, especially large trees. We excavated 121 root systems of various species (78) and sizes (up to 116 cm in dbh), and estimated both above-and below-ground biomass in a lowland primary dipterocarp forest in the Pasoh Forest Reserve, Peninsular Malaysia. A tree census was conducted in four research plots (each 0.2 ha) and stand-level biomass was'),
(127, 138, 'Publication', NULL, '0', '1', 'https://iforest.sisef.org/contents/?id=ifor1078-007&v=abstr', 'or30JcIAAAAJ;;', 14, '/scholar?q=info:hjLNHNVHf5kJ:scholar.google.com/&output=cite&scirp=0&hl=en', '/citations?hl=en&xsrf=&continue=/scholar%3Fq%3D%2BMarziliano,%2BP.A.,%2BColetta,%2BV.,%2BMenguzzato,%2BG.,%2BNicolaci,%2BA.,%2BPellicone,%2BG.,%2BVeltri,%2BA.,%2BEffects%2Bof%2Bplanting%2Bdensity%2Bon%2Bthe%2Bdistribution%2Bof%2Bbiomass%2Bin%2Ba%2Bdouglas-fir%2Bplantation%2Bin%2Bsouthern%2BItaly%2B(2015)%2BiForest%2BBiogeosci%2BFor,%2B8%2B(3),%2Bpp.%2B368-376%26hl%3Den%26as_sdt%3D0,33&citilm=1&json=&update_op=library_add&info=hjLNHNVHf5kJ&ei=VXOTYKS0EZD_mAHrlbi4AQ', '/scholar?cites=11060638190482043526&as_sdt=5,33&sciodt=0,33&hl=en', '/scholar?q=related:hjLNHNVHf5kJ:scholar.google.com/&scioq=+Marziliano,+P.A.,+Coletta,+V.,+Menguzzato,+G.,+Nicolaci,+A.,+Pellicone,+G.,+Veltri,+A.,+Effects+of+planting+density+on+the+distribution+of+biomass+in+a+douglas-fir+plantation+in+southern+Italy+(2015)+iForest+Biogeosci+For,+8+(3),+pp.+368-376&hl=en&as_sdt=0,33', 'Effects of planting density on the distribution of biomass in a douglas-fir plantation in southern Italy', 'PA Marziliano;V Coletta;G Menguzzato', 2015, 'iForest …', 'The effects of initial planting densities on the distribution of above-ground biomass of  Douglas-fir (Pseudotsuga menziesii [Mirb.] Franco var. menziesii) were investigated in a plantation  in southern Italy. Allometric equations designed for the plantation under study were used to estimate  above-ground biomass and in particular partitioning to stem and crown compartments. A comparison  between biomass estimated with allometric equations and biomass estimated with a constant  biomass expansion factor (BEF) from the Italian National Forest Inventory (INFC 2005) was carried'),
(128, 139, 'Publication', NULL, '0', '1', 'https://esajournals.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1890/0012-9658(1998)079[0828:CISCFA]2.0.CO;2', ';rkJ_vE0AAAAJ', 261, '/scholar?q=info:HMu9LBKv8PIJ:scholar.google.com/&output=cite&scirp=0&hl=en', '/citations?hl=en&xsrf=&continue=/scholar%3Fq%3D%2BBashkin,%2BM.A.,%2BBinkley,%2BD.,%2BChanges%2Bin%2Bsoil%2Bcarbon%2Bfollowing%2Bafforestation%2Bin%2BHawaii%2B(1998)%2BEcology,%2B79%2B(3),%2Bpp.%2B828-833%26hl%3Den%26as_sdt%3D0,33&citilm=1&json=&update_op=library_add&info=HMu9LBKv8PIJ&ei=V3OTYMXsJ5WSmgGbq7y4AQ', '/scholar?cites=17505684244184025884&as_sdt=5,33&sciodt=0,33&hl=en', '/scholar?q=related:HMu9LBKv8PIJ:scholar.google.com/&scioq=+Bashkin,+M.A.,+Binkley,+D.,+Changes+in+soil+carbon+following+afforestation+in+Hawaii+(1998)+Ecology,+79+(3),+pp.+828-833&hl=en&as_sdt=0,33', 'Changes in soil carbon following afforestation in Hawaii', 'MA Bashkin;D Binkley', 1998, 'Ecology', 'Afforestation in the tropics may sequester soil C and has been proposed as a management tool to aid in controlling rising levels of atmospheric CO2. We measured changes in soil C following afforestation of sugarcane fields with fast‐growing Eucalyptus saligna (Sm.) plantations in Hawaii. Using stable C isotopes, we estimated the contributions to changes in total soil C that were due to the loss of C from the prior cane cultivation, and to the gain of C from the new Eucalyptus plantations. Total soil C 10–13 yr after afforestation was 114 and'),
(129, 140, 'Publication', NULL, '0', '1', 'https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1111/j.1365-2486.2011.02447.x', ';;', 132, '/scholar?q=info:KVNoyb3-FDYJ:scholar.google.com/&output=cite&scirp=0&hl=en', '/citations?hl=en&xsrf=&continue=/scholar%3Fq%3D%2BWenjie,%2BW.,%2BLing,%2BQ.R.,%2BYuangang,%2BZ.,%2BDongxue,%2BS.,%2BJing,%2BA.,%2BHong-yan,%2BW.,%2BChanges%2Bin%2Bsoil%2Borganic%2Bcarbon,%2Bnitrogen,%2BpH%2Band%2Bbulk%2Bdensity%2Bwith%2Bthe%2Bdevelopment%2Bof%2Blarch%2B(Larix%2Bgmelinii)%2Bplantations%2Bin%2BChina%2B(2011)%2BGlob%2BChang%2BBiol,%2B17%2B(8),%2Bpp.%2B2657-2676%26hl%3Den%26as_sdt%3D0,33&citilm=1&json=&update_op=library_add&info=KVNoyb3-FDYJ&ei=WXOTYL26N4LCsQKw15L4DA', '/scholar?cites=3897019668663653161&as_sdt=5,33&sciodt=0,33&hl=en', '/scholar?q=related:KVNoyb3-FDYJ:scholar.google.com/&scioq=+Wenjie,+W.,+Ling,+Q.R.,+Yuangang,+Z.,+Dongxue,+S.,+Jing,+A.,+Hong-yan,+W.,+Changes+in+soil+organic+carbon,+nitrogen,+pH+and+bulk+density+with+the+development+of+larch+(Larix+gmelinii)+plantations+in+China+(2011)+Glob+Chang+Biol,+17+(8),+pp.+2657-2676&hl=en&as_sdt=0,33', 'Changes in soil organic carbon, nitrogen, pH and bulk density with the development of larch (Larix gmelinii) plantations in China', 'W WEN‐JIE;Q Ling;ZU YUAN‐GANG', 2011, 'Global change …', 'Under the government of China\'s environmental program known as Returning Farmland To Forests (RFTF), about 28 million hectares of farmland have been converted to tree plantation. This has led to a large accumulation of biomass carbon, but less is known about underground carbon‐related processes. One permanent plot (25 years of observation) and four chronosequence plot series comprising 159 plots of larch (Larix gmelinii) plantations in northeastern China were studied. Both methods found significant soil organic carbon (SOC)'),
(130, 141, 'Publication', NULL, '0', '1', 'https://www.narcis.nl/publication/RecordID/oai:dare.uva.nl:publications%2F2302f336-b627-4b39-b6af-213844894ecd', ';;', 35, '/scholar?q=info:B0XxkIk9v14J:scholar.google.com/&output=cite&scirp=0&hl=en', '/citations?hl=en&xsrf=&continue=/scholar%3Fq%3D%2BHofstede,%2BR.G.M.,%2BCoppus,%2BR.,%2BV%25C3%2583%25C2%25A1sconez,%2BP.M.,%2BSegarra,%2BP.,%2BWolf,%2BJ.,%2BThe%2Bconservation%2Bstatus%2Bof%2Btussock%2Bgrass%2Bparamo%2Bin%2BEcuador%2B(2002)%2BEcotopicos,%2B15%2B(1),%2Bpp.%2B3-18%26hl%3Den%26as_sdt%3D0,33&citilm=1&json=&update_op=library_add&info=B0XxkIk9v14J&ei=XHOTYMWzCOTTsQLdgI_YAw', '/scholar?cites=6827243221168506119&as_sdt=5,33&sciodt=0,33&hl=en', '/scholar?q=related:B0XxkIk9v14J:scholar.google.com/&scioq=+Hofstede,+R.G.M.,+Coppus,+R.,+V%C3%83%C2%A1sconez,+P.M.,+Segarra,+P.,+Wolf,+J.,+The+conservation+status+of+tussock+grass+paramo+in+Ecuador+(2002)+Ecotopicos,+15+(1),+pp.+3-18&hl=en&as_sdt=0,33', 'The conservation status of tussock grass paramo in Ecuador', 'RGM Hofstede;R Coppus;P Mena Vásconez', 2002, 'Ecotropicos', 'Title, The conservation status of tussock grass paramo in Ecuador. Published in, Ecotropicos, 15(1), 3 - 18. Sociedad Venezolano de Ecologia. ISSN 1012-1692. Author, Hofstede, RGM; Coppus, R.; Mena Vasconez, P.; Segarra, P.; Wolf, JHD; Sevink, J. Publisher, Experimental Plant Systematics (IBED, FNWI); Paleoecology and Landscape Ecology (IBED, FNWI). Date issued, 2002. Access, Restricted Access. Language, und. Type, Article. Publisher, Sociedad Venezolano de Ecologia. Publication, https://dare.uva.nl/personal/pure/en/publications');
